    <sectiondef kind="user-defined">
      <header>GPIO drive strength flags</header>
      <description><para>The drive strength flags are a Zephyr specific extension of the standard GPIO flags specified by the Linux GPIO binding.</para>
<para>Only applicable for Espressif ESP32 SoCs.</para>
<para>The interface supports two different drive strengths: <computeroutput>DFLT</computeroutput> - The highest drive strength supported by the HW <computeroutput>ALT</computeroutput> - The lowest drive strength supported by the HW </para>
</description>
